		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 24th 11:23 AM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1111660459530331144&num=21&post=1&replyto=1111681357215788626"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1111681357215788626></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=369727"><span id=>Paradime</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />52 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.91]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Paradime&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Sypherr,<br><br>Buying a new computer is a BIG investment, and you should take your time and do your home work! Take the advice from the board. But with a grain of salt.<br><br>Dells are great for peeps that want to run Turbo Tax and Microsoft Word at home. What your not going to get with a Dell the ability to RUN your system. I just don’t think they use the best parts they can. You can do better.<br><br>Green-Box aka AlienWare… To much hype and way I mean way over priced !!! But better than a Dell.<br><br>So what’s that leave… Build your own computer. You will be happy with it. You’ll take pride in your creation, and learn about what makes it tick. Most of all it’s fun.<br><br>Sites you are going to need to build your computer <br><br>www.exoxide.com <br>This site has great cases. <br>www.newegg.com<br>Every thing elts you’r going to need.<br><br>I built my last computer around December 04. I’ll lay out some specs to give you some thing to go on.<br><br>The first thing to find is your CPU. Most every thing is going to build off of this chose.<br>I went with the AMD Athlon 64 3500+, 512K, L2 Cache, Socket 939. This CPU is 64 bit compatible. This is a big plus. Micrsoft’s next OS will be 64bit. Release date some time in 06. <br><br>Now you need to find a Motherboard. If you’re running a 939 chip, you’ll have to find a 939 Motherboard. I went with this one. MSI &quot;K8N Neo2 Platinum&quot; NVIDIA nForce3 ULTRA Chipset Motherboard For AMD Socket 939. This is a GREAT motherboard. *NOTE* I made this computer before PCIX and SLI. If you build a computer GET PCI-Express. It’s a must have for the new video cards.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Get your self some RAM. I went with this Corsair 184pin 512 x 4 giving me 2GB of RAM.<br><br>Hard drives: For your OS and Games get a Western Digital Raptor. This is a SATA hard drive but most mother boards are SATA now. Also this hard drive spins at 10,000 RPM the seek time is fast. For your data got with a Western Digital 200GB it spins slower, but your not running apps off of it.<br><br>Computer case LL Warrior (Black) from www.xoxide.com this is the case I use. And I have no regrets.<br><br>This should give you a starting point. But do some home work. Don’t run out and buy a Dell. You’ll be much happy if you build your computer.<br><br>I hope this helps.<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
